{"article_id":"WyCYiWYtBLW7WjZy","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"MONROVIA , Liberia -","depth":1},{"id":1,"text":"Aid workers are rushing into neighboring Guinea","depth":5},{"id":2,"text":"to try to stanch a worrisome rise in cases of the deadly Ebola virus ,","depth":6},{"id":3,"text":"which has been slowed in Sierra Leone","depth":7},{"id":4,"text":"and been all but eradicated here .","depth":7},{"id":5,"text":"The mission is urgent","depth":5},{"id":6,"text":"because the coming rainy season could hamper travel to remote villages","depth":6},{"id":7,"text":"where the disease continues to emerge .","depth":6},{"id":8,"text":"`` I 'm nervous but optimistic at heart","depth":6},{"id":9,"text":"that Guinea will follow the same trajectory '' as Liberia and Sierra Leone","depth":7},{"id":10,"text":"where the disease has declined ,","depth":7},{"id":11,"text":"said Jordan Tappero , director of the division of global health protection for the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention","depth":6},{"id":12,"text":"( CDC ) .","depth":6},{"id":13,"text":"`` We 've tripled the number of people","depth":9},{"id":14,"text":"we have in the field","depth":9},{"id":15,"text":"( in Guinea )","depth":8},{"id":16,"text":"and many other organizations are doing the same , ''","depth":7},{"id":17,"text":"he said .","depth":6},{"id":18,"text":"`` We 've got to keep pressing on","depth":6},{"id":19,"text":"and stay with it . ''","depth":6},{"id":20,"text":"Nearly 25,000 people across West Africa have been infected with Ebola","depth":7},{"id":21,"text":"since the disease surfaced in the jungles of Guinea in December 2013 .","depth":7},{"id":22,"text":"More than 10,000 have died in the worst outbreak of the disease in history .","depth":6},{"id":23,"text":"The 95 new cases","depth":8},{"id":24,"text":"reported during the week of March 15","depth":8},{"id":25,"text":"was the highest weekly total for the nation so far this year .","depth":7},{"id":26,"text":"This week , only 45 new cases were reported .","depth":6},{"id":27,"text":"Still troubling to World Health Organization workers is how new infections in Guinea are occurring in unexpected areas .","depth":5},{"id":28,"text":"Many of the outbreaks are in distant villages ,","depth":6},{"id":29,"text":"and only 38 % of new infections in Guinea last week were among people","depth":8},{"id":30,"text":"being tracked .","depth":8},{"id":31,"text":"The week before , the figure was 28 %","depth":9},{"id":32,"text":"- a low rate","depth":10},{"id":33,"text":"that is foreboding","depth":10},{"id":34,"text":"because it means healthcare workers are n't effectively establishing a chain of infection .","depth":8},{"id":35,"text":"A crucial element","depth":8},{"id":36,"text":"in defeating the virus","depth":8},{"id":37,"text":"is the process of contact tracing","depth":9},{"id":38,"text":"- tracking all","depth":10},{"id":39,"text":"who have been exposed","depth":10},{"id":40,"text":"so that chain can be broken","depth":9},{"id":41,"text":"and the disease can be halted .","depth":9},{"id":42,"text":"Tracing contacts in new infections will become even more difficult","depth":9},{"id":43,"text":"when the rainy season begins in June","depth":10},{"id":44,"text":"and downpours happen daily by July ,","depth":10},{"id":45,"text":"Tappero said.","depth":8},{"id":46,"text":"`` That 's why we have to get down to as close to zero with contact tracing all known , laboratory confirmed cases by then , ''","depth":9},{"id":47,"text":"he said .","depth":9},{"id":48,"text":"`` I 'll be honest with you ,","depth":9},{"id":49,"text":"people are fatigued . ''","depth":9},{"id":50,"text":"In nearby Sierra Leone ,","depth":8},{"id":51,"text":"where more than 3,700 have died","depth":9},{"id":52,"text":"and almost 12,000 were infected ,","depth":9},{"id":53,"text":"the nation 's 6 million residents have been ordered to stay home for three days","depth":9},{"id":54,"text":"beginning Friday ,","depth":9},{"id":55,"text":"except for religious services , in an effort","depth":9},{"id":56,"text":"to fight the spread of the disease ,","depth":9},{"id":57,"text":"according to Associated Press .","depth":6},{"id":58,"text":"Earlier this month , an American health worker ill with Ebola was evacuated from Sierra Leone to the United States","depth":10},{"id":59,"text":"and remains in critical condition at the National Institutes of Health in Bethesda , Md .","depth":10},{"id":60,"text":"The worker was among 12 new Ebola infections","depth":10},{"id":61,"text":"involving caregivers in Sierra Leone and Guinea in the past few weeks .","depth":10},{"id":62,"text":"Nearly 500 healthcare workers across West Africa have died of the disease","depth":10},{"id":63,"text":"since the outbreak began .","depth":10},{"id":64,"text":"In Guinea , the workers affected are often a remote village 's only nurse or doctor .","depth":9},{"id":65,"text":"`` We really need the rate of healthcare infections to be zero , ''","depth":8},{"id":66,"text":"said Ian Norton , a physician with the World Health Organization .","depth":8},{"id":67,"text":"New infections in Sierra Leone are slowly diminishing ,","depth":8},{"id":68,"text":"WHO reported .","depth":8},{"id":69,"text":"Last week 84 % of the 33 new cases were among people","depth":10},{"id":70,"text":"health officials were tracking","depth":10},{"id":71,"text":"- good news ,","depth":10},{"id":72,"text":"WHO said","depth":10},{"id":73,"text":"because it shows","depth":9},{"id":74,"text":"health workers are successfully identifying and isolating those","depth":10},{"id":75,"text":"who might become infected .","depth":10},{"id":76,"text":"In Liberia , infections fell dramatically ,","depth":9},{"id":77,"text":"dropping to zero for three straight weeks this month .","depth":9},{"id":78,"text":"Beaches and schools re-opened .","depth":9},{"id":79,"text":"Students showed up","depth":10},{"id":80,"text":"to have their temperatures taken","depth":11},{"id":81,"text":"and wash hands","depth":12},{"id":82,"text":"before entering class .","depth":12},{"id":83,"text":"More than 4,200 of those","depth":10},{"id":84,"text":"killed by the virus were in Liberia","depth":10},{"id":85,"text":"where President Obama deployed about 3,000 troops","depth":10},{"id":86,"text":"to build clinics","depth":11},{"id":87,"text":"and train health care workers late last year .","depth":11},{"id":88,"text":"About 300 troops remain there .","depth":8},{"id":89,"text":"There has been at least one setback .","depth":10},{"id":90,"text":"A ban on sporting activities was lifted","depth":11},{"id":91,"text":"and the first soccer match was underway in Monrovia March 20 with President Ellen Johnson Sirleaf in attendance","depth":12},{"id":92,"text":"when word of a new Ebola case broke .","depth":12},{"id":93,"text":"A 44-year-old mother of six","depth":13},{"id":94,"text":"who worked as a food server at a school","depth":13},{"id":95,"text":"fell ill.","depth":12},{"id":96,"text":"She rode on a motorbike-taxi to the hospital , a common means of transportation in Monrovia , Liberia 's capital .","depth":11},{"id":97,"text":"One small school","depth":14},{"id":98,"text":"where she worked","depth":14},{"id":99,"text":"has been temporarily closed .","depth":13},{"id":100,"text":"Eighty-six people","depth":14},{"id":101,"text":"who were in contact with her","depth":14},{"id":102,"text":"have been quarantined .","depth":13},{"id":103,"text":"The woman died Friday ,","depth":12},{"id":104,"text":"Reuters reported .","depth":12},{"id":105,"text":"The Ministry of Health is looking into","depth":10},{"id":106,"text":"whether the disease might have been transmitted through sexual contact with an Ebola survivor .","depth":10},{"id":107,"text":"Although the man","depth":12},{"id":108,"text":"she was dating","depth":12},{"id":109,"text":"was released from care more than three months before ,","depth":11},{"id":110,"text":"research has found","depth":11},{"id":111,"text":"that the virus can survive in male sexual organs for an extended period of time .","depth":11},{"id":112,"text":"`` We were getting close to the finishing line","depth":10},{"id":113,"text":"when this sad event occurred , ''","depth":10},{"id":114,"text":"said Liberian government spokesman Isaac Jackson .","depth":9},{"id":115,"text":"`` We are all saddened by this development .","depth":9},{"id":116,"text":"But we are consoled","depth":10},{"id":117,"text":"because we have in place the best system , surveillance , contact tracers ,","depth":11},{"id":118,"text":"so we are still committed to beating this virus . ''","depth":11}],"relations":[{"parent":237,"left":0,"right":236,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":236,"left":137,"right":235,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":137,"left":125,"right":136,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":125,"left":122,"right":124,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":122,"left":1,"right":121,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":121,"left":2,"right":120,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":120,"left":3,"right":4,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":124,"left":5,"right":123,"relation":"causal","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":123,"left":6,"right":7,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":136,"left":129,"right":135,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":129,"left":127,"right":128,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":127,"left":8,"right":126,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":126,"left":9,"right":10,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":128,"left":11,"right":12,"relation":"restatement","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":135,"left":133,"right":134,"relation":"evaluation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":133,"left":132,"right":17,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":132,"left":131,"right":16,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":131,"left":130,"right":15,"relation"